  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Technical Support for the BAT Development Impact Bonds Project</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Technical Assistance Grant covers three outputs that will enable this outcome and impact to be achieved: 1. Operational costs for the DIB: the essential management and monitoring costs that will ensure the DIB can achieve its intended outcomes. 2. Learning and evidence-based knowledge generation: development of the resources, tools, knowledge and partnerships necessary to generate and share learning from this DIB. 3. Replication: development of the resources, tools, and partnerships to successfully adapt and replicate this DIB in other sectors and/or geographies.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The intended Impact of the requested Technical Assistance Grant from DFID is to support the launch of at least one new DIB, thereby demonstrating the potential of DIBs to unlock new forms of social finance capital and shift focus from inputs to outcomes delivery. The intended Outcome is to create a stable financing tool for learning, scaling and replication of Impact Bonds.</narrative>
  </description>
